    "# Best Subset Example with Python\n",
    "\n",
    "**Exhaustive Feature Selector (EFS)** will try **all possible subsets of predictors** between size 1 and 11.\n",
    "\n",
    "- That means for each $k$ (number of predictors), it fits all $\\binom{p}{k}$ models.\n",
    "\n",
    "**For each candidate model**, it performs **5-fold cross-validation (cv=5)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "- The data is split into 5 folds.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Each fold is used once as a validation set, while the other 4 folds are used for training.\n",
    "\n",
    "- The average $R^2$ across the 5 folds is computed.\n",
    "\n",
    "The model's performance is then compared to the other candidate models, and the **best subset(s)** are identified.\n"
   ]
