   "source": [
    "## Backward Sequential Feature Selection Arguments\n",
    "\n",
    "| Argument | Meaning | Example / Analogy |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **`estimator=model`** | Specifies the base model used to evaluate each feature subset, such as `LinearRegression()`. | Like choosing the engine that powers the feature-selection process. |\n",
    "| **`k_features='best'`** | Tells the selector to identify the feature subset with the best cross-validation performance rather than fixing the number of selected features in advance. | Like allowing the coach to determine the best team size based on performance. |\n",
    "| **`forward=False`** | Uses **backward selection**. The process starts with all predictors and removes one predictor at each step. | Like starting with a full team and removing one player at a time until the best lineup is found. |\n",
    "| **`floating=False`** | Disables floating selection. A feature removed during backward selection is not reconsidered at a later step. | Once a player is removed from the team, the player cannot return. |\n",
    "| **`scoring='r2'`** | Uses $R^2$ to evaluate and compare the predictive performance of the candidate regression models. | Like ranking teams according to their performance score. |\n",
    "| **`cv=5`** | Uses **5-fold cross-validation**. Each candidate model is evaluated using five different training and validation splits. | Like testing the team’s performance across five different matches. |"
   ]
